# MASTER PROMPT — MTK GALLERY BUILDER

Act as a senior Vanilla JavaScript application architect and production UI/UX engineer.

Build a complete gallery application named `mtk-gallery` for selling hand-painted artwork.

Use this repository as the base:

https://github.com/NYCMEL/nala-website.git

Use ALL wc utility functionality including:

* `wc-include`
* `wc.publish`
* `wc.subscribe`
* `wc.log`
* event helpers

from this file:

https://github.com/NYCMEL/nala-website/blob/main/js/_wc.js

---

# OUTPUT RULES

* Return ONLY one downloadable ZIP file named exactly: `x.zip`
* Never show code in chat
* Never return patch files or diffs
* Always return complete files only
* Never modify anything outside the scope of this request
* Never generate placeholder explanations instead of files
* Never create images unless explicitly requested

---

# REQUIRED FILES

Generate exactly these files:

* index.html

Single-file GitHub Pages deployment only.

Everything must exist inside:

* HTML
* CSS
* JavaScript
* config JSON
* admin logic
* gallery rendering

inside ONE standalone file.

---

# GITHUB.IO RULES

Application MUST run directly from:

* GitHub Pages
* local browser
* static hosting
* file://

DO NOT:

* require a server
* require Node.js
* require PHP
* require SQLite runtime
* require npm
* require webpack
* require build tools

Application must work immediately by opening:

index.html

---

# CORE TECH RULES

* Vanilla JavaScript only
* No frameworks
* No Bootstrap
* No React
* No Vue
* No Angular
* No external libraries
* No inline event handlers
* No SCSS loading in browser
* CSS must be embedded directly in `<style>`
* JavaScript must be embedded directly in `<script>`
* Never use iframes
* No recursive rendering
* No DOM wipe loops
* No blinking screen behavior
* Prevent double initialization

---

# COMPONENT ARCHITECTURE

Component wrapper:

<mtk-gallery class="mtk-gallery"></mtk-gallery>

Rules:

* Root class must be `.mtk-gallery`
* Scope ALL styles under `.mtk-gallery`
* No global IDs
* Use semantic HTML only
* ADA compliant
* Keyboard accessible
* responsive design
* Visible focus states required

---

# CONFIG + DATA RULES

ALL UI-driven data MUST come from embedded config JSON.

Paintings must support:

* id
* title
* description
* image
* price
* availability
* dimensions
* medium
* category
* PayPal data

Store owner must be able to:

* change paintings
* change prices
* change availability
* change images
* change details

Data persistence must use:

* localStorage

for GitHub Pages compatibility.

---

# IMAGE REQUIREMENTS

Include:

* original starter paintings
* PLUS 20 additional random artwork images

Requirements:

* high-quality artwork images
* use remote image URLs
* responsive image handling
* object-fit cover
* gallery-ready presentation

---

# EVENT SYSTEM RULES

Wait for `<mtk-gallery>` to exist before initializing.

Requirements:

* Subscribe to all `4-mtk-gallery` events using `wc.subscribe`
* Create `onMessage()` handler
* Publish actions using `wc.publish`
* Log ALL payloads using `wc.log` BEFORE publishing
* Prevent duplicate initialization
* Prevent recursive render loops
* Prevent blank screen behavior
* Ensure render happens once unless explicitly refreshed

---

# GALLERY UI

Header title:

`Madam Mina's Artwork`

Layout requirements:

* `.mtk-gallery` background = `#FFF`
* `.mtk-gallery__shell`
  * `max-inline-size: 1200px`

Home screen:

* display painting cards only
* NO buttons on cards

Painting card requirements:

* image
* title
* category
* price
* status badge

Status badge text:

* Available
* Sold

DO NOT use:

* Unavailable!

---

# DETAIL VIEW

Painting click behavior:

* opens FULL-SCREEN detail overlay
* overlay covers entire application
* include circular close button with “X”
* support ESC key close

Detail view includes:

* image
* title
* description
* price
* availability
* dimensions
* medium
* category
* artwork ID
* actions

---

# SALES + REQUEST FLOWS

## Available Paintings

Show:

* Buy with PayPal
* “Make me a counter offer”

Behavior:

* clicking link reveals counter-offer form
* form hidden by default

## Sold Paintings

Show:

* “Request a similar painting”

Behavior:

* clicking link reveals request form
* form hidden by default

